pnpm  pnpm is a fast and disk space efficient package manager, serving as an alternative to npm and yarn.   Ensure you have   installed Node.js .  Open a command-line terminal (e.g. Terminal, Command Prompt).  Enter   npm install -g pnpm  to globally install the package.  You can install dependencies with pnpm using   pnpm i .  You can reference   package.json  files for available scripts, i.e.     "scripts"  : {
   "start"  :   "vite"  ,
   "watch"  :   "vite build --watch"  ,
   "build"  :   "tsc && vite build"  ,
   "preview"  :   "vite preview"  ,
   "format"  :   "prettier --write   \"  ./src/**/*.{ts,tsx,css}  \"  "
 },
